fields.Title: LANDS END ORB / lands end shot viscal
fields.Condition: Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_cancelled"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end"]  and  Variable["coast.sense_perc_campfire_remains"]  and  Variable["coast.sense_perc_latter_on_tower"]  and  Variable["coast.orb_lands_end_shot_done"] == false
fields.Description: the conclusion dialogue where you conclude the shot did not come from land's end. this fires only if you have  TASK.check_lands_end

fields.Title: You: "Maybe the assailant climbed the com..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe the assailant climbed the comms tower, took the shot there?
fields.Alternate1: "Maybe the assailant climbed the comms tower, took the shoot there?"

fields.Title: You: "What about the cigarette butts?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What about the cigarette butts?

fields.Title: You: ""Copsicle. You meant to say copsicl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Copsicle. You meant to say copsicle."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Nothing is unimportant, detective."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing is unimportant, detective.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Those?" He points to them. "A smok..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Those?" He points to them. "A smoking assailant who favours Tioumoutiri to Astra or Drouin? Cigarette butts are everywhere. This is a common brand for old men."

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. I should look into t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. I should look into this situation before I die of hypothermia."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The light is off on the third floor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The light is off on the third floor of the Whirling-in-Rags. The young woman is gone who knows where. Safe, closed off. Her form no longer moves behind the glass there...

fields.Title: You: "Look over the water -- to the Whirl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look over the water -- to the Whirling-in-Rags.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Truthfully -- this seems like a ve..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Truthfully -- this seems like a very poor choice to take a 1.2 kilometre rifle shot from. Visibility is awful, there's water vapour everywhere -- I think we can rule out... B double prime, was it?"

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Smoking. Drinking. Being happy and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smoking. Drinking. Being happy and elated. Without you -- because you're here, freezing in the wind, aren't you? Doing your *detective work*.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "There, 1.2 kilometres over the cold..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There, 1.2 kilometres over the cold water of the bay, through a thick snowstorm melting flake by flake in the waves you see the smallest rectangle, barely visible.

fields.Title: You: ""Kim, you look cold -- maybe a thic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim, you look cold -- maybe a thicker coat?"

fields.Title: You: "Oh right..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh right...

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Such a good girl, you think."
fields.Dialogue Text: Such a good girl, you think.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Oh, you do! The butts you saw had a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh, you do! The butts you saw had a silhouette of a boy wearing a kofia hat -- a tobacco picker. This boy is the Tioumoutiri brand logo. Contemporary Revacholians prefer Drouin (a local blend from the southern islands) or Astra, a legendary cigarette from Graad. Tioumoutiri is favoured by older men who like its old fashioned paper filter tips, insane amount of tar and the sweet smells of colonialism and halva.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No, an orange pilot cap would not..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, an orange pilot cap would not help." He turns to face the sea.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'm okay. You on the other hand --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm okay. You on the other hand -- look like you're about to turn into a popsicle."
fields.Alternate1: "I'm okay. You on the other hand, yefreitor... you look like you're about to turn into a popsicle."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That seems smart, yes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That seems smart, yes."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "There, 1.2 kilometres over the cold..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There, 1.2 kilometres over the cold water of the bay, blue from the distance and the air, you see the smallest rectangle, barely visible.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Is there something here that would..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is there something here that would indicate a sniper used this place as a nest for taking the shot? Just some urban detritus, a bottle and a dilapidated old comms tower.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Tioumoutiri was a Revacholian colon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tioumoutiri was a Revacholian colony on Iilmaraa. The suzerainty's population was mostly Iilmaraan Areopagites -- up to 97%. The region was known for its tobacco export. Hence the name.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Technically speaking that would be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Technically speaking that would be a...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The light is off on the third floor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The light is off on the third floor of the Whirling-in-Rags. The young woman is gone, in Precinct 57. Safe, closed off. Her form no longer moves behind the glass there...
"No, an orange pilot cap would not help." He turns to face the sea.
fields.Alternate1: "No, a black pilot cap would not help." He turns to face the sea.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "How do you respond to a pithy *no*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: How do you respond to a pithy *no* like that? He's just *not* into pilot caps, it seems.

fields.Title: Endurance: "He looks like he's cold out here at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He looks like he's cold out here at the tip of the coast. The jacket is warm, but not for this weather.

fields.Title: You: "I said finish the god damn thought...."
fields.Dialogue Text: I said finish the god damn thought.[Leave.]
"No what -- an orange pilot cap would not help?"
fields.Alternate1: "No what -- a black pilot cap would not help?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No. I did not. We *Seolites* don't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. I did not. We *Seolites* don't do paranomastic humour."

fields.Title: You: "[Finish thought.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Finish thought.]

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "So?"
fields.Dialogue Text: So?

fields.Title: You: ""No what -- an orange pilot cap wou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No what -- an orange pilot cap would not help?"

fields.Title: Endurance: "The wind picks up. Fine sea foam la..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The wind picks up. Fine sea foam lashes your face. It feels like needles. You can take it -- just raise your collar, detective.

fields.Title: You: "I want to know *a lot* more about t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I want to know *a lot* more about this.

fields.Title: You: "Enough. The cigarettes are unimport..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Enough. The cigarettes are unimportant.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't see it, officer. I don't s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't see it, officer. I don't see a person take a shot here and hit something there..." He looks east, over the coast. "In the Whirling-in-Rags."
fields.Alternate1: "I don't see it, lieutenant double-yefreitor. I don't see a person take a shot *here* and hit something there..." he looks east, over the coast. "In the Whirling-in-Rags."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Are you sure? You haven't ruled out..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Are you sure? You haven't ruled out the shot coming from here yet...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's not possible to climb that la..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not possible to climb that ladder and even if it were -- why? There's no platform up there to aim from." The lieutenant looks up, raising his collar.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Absolute idiocy," he nods in ackno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Absolute idiocy," he nods in acknowledgement of the idiocy on display.

fields.Title: You: "Maybe the campfire was used by the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe the campfire was used by the perpetrator?
fields.Alternate1: "Maybe the campfire was used by the perpetrator?"

fields.Title: You: ""No what -- you're not cold?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No what -- you're not cold?"

fields.Title: Perception: "In the distance you can hear the br..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In the distance you can hear the breakers roar.

fields.Title: You: ""Kim, you look cold -- maybe a litt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim, you look cold -- maybe a little pilot cap?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, that one. No to the orange pi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, that one. No to the orange pilot cap." He turns to face the sea.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Don't be silly, no one wants to be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be silly, no one wants to be a popsicle."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No."

fields.Title: You: ""It's my style. Superstar cops don'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's my style. Superstar cops don't wear parkas. They rock out."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A smoking assailant who favours Tio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A smoking assailant who favours Tioumoutiri to Astra or Drouin? Cigarette butts are part of the campfire set -- they're also everywhere.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""To warm his hands before pulling t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "To warm his hands before pulling the trigger? Perhaps. But anyone could have made this. The coast is specked with fires this time of year." He looks around.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "There, 1.2 kilometres over the wave..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There, 1.2 kilometres over the wave-crossed bay, through heavy, dark grey curtains of rain you see the smallest rectangle, barely visible.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A glowing light on the third floor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A glowing light on the third floor of the Whirling-in-Rags. With binoculars you would see a young woman's shape move behind the glass, her limbs long and slender.
"Yes, that one. No to the orange pilot cap." He turns to face the sea.
fields.Alternate1: "Yes, that one. No to the black pilot cap." He turns to face the sea.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Still, you felt it was important en..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still, you felt it was important enough to make a mental note. That means *something*. You didn't pay attention to any of the other cigarette butts on the coast.

fields.Title: You: ""What if I *want* to be a popsicle?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What if I *want* to be a popsicle?"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "It's glowing in the dark night. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's glowing in the dark night. The lights are on. Klaasje must be in there... looks like she's kept her promise not to go out at night anymore.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "To warm his hands before he pulled..."
fields.Dialogue Text: To warm his hands before he pulled the trigger? There are no markings on the ground for a tripod, he would have had to lie on a mattress. This is simply not a good spot for a 1.2 kilometre shot.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "No what?"
fields.Dialogue Text: No what?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "It's late. There is no light on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's late. There is no light on the third floor of the Whirling-in-Rags. No shape moves behind it. Klaasje must be out on the town.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "It does look *extremely* rickety. A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It does look *extremely* rickety. And wouldn't help much either.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The salty water has corroded the la..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The salty water has corroded the ladder to nothing but two thin orange rails. In addition, there is no stable nest up there. It would have been useless.
